# Cargo / Rust build artifacts.
#
# `/target/` covers any future root-level build output (none today —
# the wz Rust workspace lives under `crates/`). `crates/target/` is
# the wz workspace's own build output. `vendor/sce/target/` is the
# vendored SCE submodule's build output (submodule itself is tracked
# as a gitlink; only its target/ stays local).
/target/
crates/target/
vendor/sce/target/
# R311be — deploy/mcu-qemu-demo is a standalone workspace
# (cross-compile to thumbv7m-none-eabi); its target/ is build
# output identical in policy to crates/target/.
deploy/mcu-qemu-demo/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Cargo.lock policy: COMMITTED for the wz Rust workspace
# (`crates/Cargo.lock`) per Cargo's recommendation for binary-
# producing workspaces and for reproducible Layer 3 wire-interop
# tests across CI / dev / production. SCE submodule's lock file is
# managed by SCE. The root-level `/Cargo.lock` ignore is defensive —
# no workspace lives at the repo root today, but the rule prevents
# accidental commit if one is added later without a paired
# workspace-policy review.
/Cargo.lock

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# Mnemosyne — atomic store sidecar is workspace state; commit it (the
# audit trail lives there). GENERATED.md is derived but typically also
# committed so reviewers can read it without running the CLI.
# .atomic/  ← do NOT ignore; it IS the source of truth post Round 251.
#
# watching-zenoh hybrid carry: the 13 prose docs in mnemosyne.toml ARE
# the human-readable surface — GENERATED.md is NOT used here. Atomic
# store stays as audit-only ledger; the cascade-generated GENERATED.md
# is a byproduct of every MCP mutate primitive (MCP has no
# --no-regenerate; only mnemosyne-cli does). We don't track it.
docs/GENERATED.md

# Local Claude Code state — settings.local.json, scheduled_tasks.lock,
# transcripts, etc. Team-shared .claude/settings.json (if introduced)
# would carve out via an explicit `!.claude/settings.json` exception.
.claude/

# Activity logs (local working notes; outside mnemosyne workspace).
# Cross-session handoff lives in the atomic changelog (audit-traced);
# notes/ is a local working cache only.
notes/
